\section{Conclusion}

This specification represents the culmination of theoretical development, engineering design, and strategic planning for HLRT validation. The convergence of mathematical framework, precision measurement capability, and conservative engineering approach provides optimal conditions for definitive experimental results.

The modular tile architecture enables both proof-of-concept validation and scalable deployment, while comprehensive safety protocols ensure responsible development of potentially transformative technology.

\textbf{July 31, 2025 represents the critical inflection point between theoretical framework and empirical validation.}

The oscilloscope traces captured in a 7×7 meter garage laboratory will either confirm the discrete hexagonal structure of spacetime or provide invaluable data for theoretical refinement and experimental optimization.

\textbf{The design is complete. The components are ordered. The timeline is established.}

